signature_matches.name: stealth_network
signature_matches.description: Network activity detected but not expressed in monitor API logs
Sample drops PE files which have not been started,
Queries the volume information (name, serial number etc) of a device
Sample tries to load a library which is not present or installed on the analysis machine, adding the library might reveal more behavior
Uses HTTPS for network communication, use the 'Proxy HTTPS (port 443) to read its encrypted data' cookbook for further analysis
Found dropped PE file which has not been started or loaded
Sample searches for specific file, try point organization specific fake files to the analysis machine
May try to detect the virtual machine to hinder analysis (VM artifact strings found in memory)
Creates a process in suspended mode (likely to inject code)
Binary contains paths to debug symbols
URLs found in memory or binary data
Creates files inside the user directory

sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects a Python process initiating a network connection. While this often relates to package installation, it can also indicate a potential malicious script communicating with a C&C server.

mitre_attack_techniques.signature_description: Adversaries may communicate using application layer protocols to avoid detection/network filtering by blending in with existing traffic.
Adversaries may delete or modify artifacts generated within systems to remove evidence of their presence or hinder defenses.
Adversaries may delete files left behind by the actions of their intrusion activity.
Creates files inside the user directory
May try to detect the virtual machine to hinder analysis (VM artifact strings found in memory)
Queries the volume information (name, serial number etc) of a device
Uses HTTPS for network communication, use the SSL MITM Proxy cookbook for further analysis
